{"questionId":"9076233","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A constant force of 50.0 N is applied tangentially to the outer edge of a merry-go-round. The following diagram shows the view from above.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4698/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-11_om_06.31.00.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ1/06\"></p>\n<p>The merry-go-round has a moment of inertia of 450 kg m<sup>2</sup> about a vertical axis. The merry-go-round has a diameter of 4.00 m.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The merry-go-round starts from rest and the force is applied for one complete revolution.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate, for the merry-go-round after one revolution,&nbsp;the angular speed.&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\omega _t^2 - \\omega _0^2 = 2\\alpha \\Delta \\theta \">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi>ω</mi>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi>ω</mi>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>α</mi>\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\omega _t^2 - 0 = 2 \\times 0.22 \\times 2\\pi \">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi>ω</mi>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.22</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\omega _t} = 1.7\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>ω</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.7</mn>\n</math></span> <strong>«</strong>rads<sup>–1</sup><str